                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d55">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">704.9394/3: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-01-23T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 23, 1938—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>21. Your 48, January 22, 11 a.m. The Department suggests that, in order to avoid
                    misunderstanding, you substitute for the phrase, “that they would be prepared to
                    lend their good offices in any emergency”, the following phrase: “that, without
                    assuming representative functions, they would be prepared to render all
                    appropriate assistance, temporarily, in any emergency”.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
